git init
git add README.md
git commit -m first commit
git branch -M main
git remote add origin https://github.com/mudit-pati/Accelerated-CSFundamentals.git
git push -u origin main
rm rf .git: to convert a git repo to normal folder. .git is hidden but the command will work
git add will start tracking the file for the repo
git commit will 'stage' the change to the repo
git push will finally push it to the origin or remote repo. Best way to do it is git push origin main. Main refers to the branch name

